We also evaluated the relative degree of inflammation, necrosis (Fig. 4
) and viral antigen level (Fig. 5
) in the brains of vaccinated, ZPC738 challenged mice at day 3 and day 7 post-infection. Semi-quantitative analysis of the histopathology and immunohistochemistry results is presented in Table 2
. On day 3 post-infection, γδ TCR-deficient mice exhibited an inflammatory response comparable to other groups of vaccinated, immunodeficient mouse strains tested, in addition to slightly more extensive tissue necrosis, which was comparable to that of mock-vaccinated WT control mice. In αβ TCR-deficient mice, the extent of inflammation and necrosis was at an intermediate level relative to mock vaccinated WT and vaccinated γδ TCR-deficient mice (Table 2).
